        <section>
            <h2>What is Basketball?</h2>
            <p>Basketball is a fast-paced sport where two teams of five players compete to score points by shooting a ball through the opposing team's hoop. The game is played on a rectangular court, and players use a variety of skills including dribbling, passing, and shooting.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Key Players and Positions</h2>
            <p>There are five main positions in basketball: Point Guard, Shooting Guard, Small Forward, Power Forward, and Center. Each position has a unique role on the court, ranging from handling the ball to protecting the basket.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Why Basketball is Popular</h2>
            <p>Basketball is one of the most popular sports worldwide, known for its excitement, teamwork, and high-intensity action. It's played by millions of people in schools, neighborhoods, and professional leagues.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Fun Facts about Basketball</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Basketball was invented in 1891 by Dr. James Naismith.</li>
                <li>The NBA is the most well-known professional basketball league globally.</li>
                <li>Michael Jordan is widely considered the greatest basketball player of all time.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Famous Basketball Teams</h2>
